<A>__{mickey shrugs.}
<C>__{galvin}
<D>__{we're doing fine.}
<B>__{angle}
<A>__{the two of them crossing the lobby. dick doneghy, looking around the lobby, spies them, starts across, and accosts galvin.}
<C>__{doneghy}
<D>__{you said you're gonna call me up. you didn't call me up. who do you think you are?}
<P>__{(pushes galvin into a}
<D>__{wall; advances; pushes}
<P>__{him again)}
<D>__{who do you think you are...?}
<C>__{galvin}
<D>__{hold on a second.}
<C>__{doneghy}
<D>__{i'm going to have you disbarred. i'm going to have your ticket. you know what you did? do you know what you did?}
<A>__{he pushes galvin again. galvin waves mickey off.}
<C>__{galvin}
<D>__{it's all right, mickey.}
<C>__{doneghy}
<D>__{you ruined my life, mister... me and my wife... and i am going to ruin yours...}
<P>__{(pushes galvin again)}
<D>__{you don't have to go out there to see that girl. we been going four years.}
<P>__{(beat)}
<D>__{four years... my wife's been crying herself to sleep what they, what, what they did to her sister.}
<C>__{galvin}
<D>__{i swear to you i wouldn't have turned the offer down unless i thought that i could win the case...}
<C>__{doneghy}
<D>__{what you thought!? what you thought... i'm a workingman, i'm trying to get my wife out of town, we hired you, we're paying you, i got to find out from the other side they offered two hundred...}
<C>__{galvin}
<D>__{i'm going to win this case... mist... mr. doneghy... i'm going to the jury with a solid case, a famous doctor as an expert witness, and i'm going to win eight hundred thousand dollars.}
<C>__{doneghy}
